      "content": "i guess i see what u mean about long term stuff, but it feels like u're assuming every shop has the extra cash to \"innovate\" right when they're being hit with new fees. isn't it true that for a lot of these struggling local businesses, these regulations are basically just an ideological move by the govt that prioritizes environmental goals over the actual survival of the local manufacturing sector?",
