      "content": "While you are right that some smaller businesses lack the capital to absorb sudden compliance costs, many of these regulations specifically include \"small business set-aside\" programs or phased-in timelines designed to prevent job losses. Critics argue the mandates lack flexibility, but supporting data shows that proactive adaptation often leads to cost savings on waste disposal and energy, rather than just immediate financial hemorrhaging. The goal of the legislation is to balance environmental protection with economic stability, though implementation gaps can certainly feel unfair to struggling owners right now.",
